manifests/keymaster.pp.message: Should we really enforce default value of 1 here?
doing with the lowest common value is probably best

The version of 1 is the safest. ie: the proxies are going to write version 1 of the crypto metadata, which is compatible with older Swift releases, so it will work when upgrading. However, one can use version 3 if all proxies are upgraded.

So I do believe that a default of 1 is the most sensitive value we can have.

Another possibility would be to force our users to set a value, and crash if none is provided. That's not backward compatible though, but that's probably what we want, as this is a quite touchy parameter.

Your thoughts are welcome.
